post_text: Congratulations Kadarious!
shared_text:
Kimberly Taylor is with Ashanti Smith.
May 19 at 2:42 PM ·

Congratulations Kadarious on winning a laptop. I taught my children to always remember who helped them along the way. Many people have poured into my children and I am so proud of my middle daughter Lafaye for stepping up to help our youth by providing laptops. Kadarious Griggs Is a Senior at Quitman County High School, and he won the May 22nd laptop giveaway. He will continue his journey in the US Army Reserve as an IT Specialist. GO KADARIOUS! The sky is the limit!

post_text:
May 1st is National School Principals' Day!

Mr. Jon Erik Jones is the outstanding principal of Quitman County Pre-K through 12 school.

Mr. Jones can be described as a Transformational Leader with a unique ability to build stakeholder teams in an effort to solve the challenges that we often face in education.

Please join me in celebrating Mr. Jon Erik Jones! Thanks for all that you do.

For the Children,
Mrs. Victoria L. Harris, Ed.S
Superintendent

post_text:
QCS Family,
It is with a great deal of sadness that we report the loss of a valuable & precious member of our team. Ms. Patricia Thornton (“Ms. Katie”) passed away this morning.
Ms. Katie has been a valuable member of the QC team for over 40 years. She was truly loved by everyone that knew her and will be missed. We ask that you keep Ms. Katie’s family in your thoughts and prayers.

Rest In Peace Ms. Katie

QCS Family,
It is with a great deal of sadness that we report the loss of a valuable & precious member of our team. Ms. Patricia Thornton (“Ms. Katie”) passed away this morning.
Ms. Katie has been a valuable member of the QC team for over 40 years. She was truly loved by everyone that knew her and will be missed. We ask that you keep Ms. Katie’s family in your thoughts and prayers.

Rest In Peace Ms. Katie
